HEADWORD: Ostentate
<hw>Os"ten*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ostentatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>ostentare</ets>, v. intens. fr.
<ets>ostendere</ets>. See <er>Ostent</er>.]</ety> <def>To make an
ambitious display of; to show or exhibit boastingly.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

